{"/service/ndnp/ncu/batch_ncu_dill_ver02/data/sn91068695/00279559447/1945091301/0300.xml":{"full_text":"THE MARION PROGRESS\nPUBLISHED EVERY THURSDAY BY THE\nMcdowell publishing co.\nMARION, N. C.\nTELEPHONE 64\nS. E. WHITTEN, Editor and Proprietor\nEntered at the Postoffice at Marion, N. C.,\nas second cl^ss matter.\nSUBSCRIPTION RATE:\nOne Year $1.50\nStrictly in Advance.\nYOUR PART IN PEACE\nNylons will soon be on store shelves again\nthe girfde supply will stretch posibili\nties for the use of the energy discovered by the\nproduction of atomic bombs seem unlimited.\nThe reconversion of industry to peace time\nneeds is the topic of conversation.\nBut what of you, your town and your coun\nty\u2014what effect will peace have on you? The\nSeptember issue of \"Coronet\" magazine cites\none peace plan vo.u can put into effect today.\nMore men are arriving in Marion and Mc\nDowell county each day from the battlefronts.\nComing back home is a dream they have cher\nished on the battlefronts, on board ships, in fox\nholes, in prison camps. Do you wonder if it is\nall they dreamed?\nDid you stop to speak to a soldier, sailor or\nmarine today when you passed him on the\nstreet? Did you thank him for fighting to save\nyou and your home from the fate of those war\ntorn countries? Is it too much to ask that you\nwelcome him home?\nIf you feel that you are not eloquent enough\nto put into words the gratitude that is in your\nheart, just a warm \"hello,\" just a word to let\nhim know he has been missed, that you are glad\nhe is home, will help.\nThose major problems of reconversion must\nbe worked out by those adept at specialized\nwork. But you have a part, this plan depends\non you. Start today! Welcome the boys back\nhome! It's little enough to ask.\nRECONVERSION\nThe armed forces are expected to release\n7,000,00 men within the year, all of whom will\nbe looking for jobs. A $35,000,000,000 cut\nback in war manufacturing has already re\nleased millions of war workers. It has been\npredicted that unemployment will reach 5,000.\n000 in October, that it may exceed 8,000,000\nbefore Spring.\nAll this has brought one all-important word\ninto the consciousness of the American people\nReconversion.\nReconversion is not just the mechanics of\nchanging manufacture over from war material\nto peacetime articles. Our nation has grown\nso enormously during the war that returning\nnow to 1939 production standards would leave\nhundreds of our plants shut down with an es\ntimated 10,000,000 unemployed.\nSuccessful reconversion means expanding\npeacetime production to staggering new highs.\nIt means making more baby carriages, flat\nirons, clothing and automobiles than we ever\ndreamed of making before. It means raising\nthe standards of living of all of America, with\nour citizens consuming more goods, and with\nmore money available for that purpose, than\never before in our history. It means shifting\nAmerica into a brand-new peacetime economy\nwhich can absorb unemployment so well and\nso swiftly that only a short time will elapse be\nfore anyone who wishes may work again.\nHow. this orderly reconversion is to be ac\ncomplished is taxing the finest brains that\nAmerican government and industry can pro\nduce. Already some of these men are point\ning to \"danger\" spots where bottlenecks can\noccur to slow down or cripple the whole plan.\nOne of the \"danger\" spots most frequently\nmentioned is pupwood production. Shortages\nin pnlpwood during this period will mean that\npaper and paperboard will not be available in\nsufficient quantities to wrap, pack and pack\nage the goods being turned out by American\nfactories. Reemployment depends on full pro\nduction; full production can only be accom\nplished if distribution can be maintained at a\nhigh level. This depends in large part on\npulpwood.\nMills in this area are urgently in need of\nmore top quality pulpwood NOW. The cord\nyou cut today means a job for someone tomor\nrow.\nThe prosperity of our country depends\nlargely, upon a prosperous agricultural popu\nlation, and, if you think differently, just watch\nand see.\n\"The law\" will do nothing by itself.\nDEMOBILIZATION PROCEEDING\nj From figures announced, it is difficult to see\nhow any American can intelligently criticize\nthe armed services for their demobilization pro\ngram.\nj The Army proposes to reduce its strength\nfrom 8,050,000 to 2,500,000 by July. The Navy\nwill drop from 3,389,000 to about 550,000 by\nnext September and the Marine Corps will re\nduce from 421,370 to about 100,000. In addi\ntion, the Army Medical Corps says it will re\nlease 13,000 of 45,000 doctors and 25,000 of\n56,000 nurses by January 1st.\nSpokesmen for the Army, Navy and Marine\nCorps have made it plain to the House Military\nAffairs Committee that they prefer the volun\nteer system, if it will supply the men needed\n!for post-war commitments. They do not favor\nabolition of Selective Service for the present,\nsaying that the voluntary method should be\ngiven a trial and that if it produces an adequate\nsupply of men, there will not be the necessity\nIfor the continuance of the draft.\nIllustrating what the services have in mind\nis the Navy's requirements of 21,000 enlisted\nmen a month. For September, the Navy has\nasked Selective Service to provide 10,000 men,\nwhich compares with 49,000 a month during\nthe war. Thus, the Navy estimates that it can\nsecure 11,000 men by voluntary recruiting\nmethods and a spokesman points out that if the\n|number of volunteers exceeds expectations, the\nI Navy will naturally reduce calls on the Select\nive Service machinery.\ni f\nALWAYS TO BE SUSPECTED\nFrom Japanese sources comes the opinion\nthat the Japanese people, by loyally cooperat- i\njing with the forces of occupation, will be able\nto convince the world of their right to associate\nwith civilized people and, in time, to have a i\ngovernment that can take a leading place!\namong the nations of the world.\nDespite the evidence of the war that has\ncome to an end, with all the atrocities that have\nbeen proved against the Japanese, there will be\nsome Americans anxious to extend the hand of\nfellowship and to give the Japanese people\ncredit for civilized impulses that are alien to\ntheir character.\nThe Japanese, it should be remembered, op\nened their war against Russia by a surprise at\ntack upon Port Arthur. They began their war\nagainst us, while diplomats were in conference\nin Washington, by a treacherous attack with\nout any declaration of war.\nIn China, and wherever the Japanese forces\nhave gone, helpless people have been mistreat\ned in horrible fashion and deliberate efforts\nwere made to degrade and punish representa\ntives of the Western nations.\nEven now, with the Allied occupation of\nJapan proceeding, there can be little confi\ndence in the apparent submission of the Japa\nnese people. Nobody knows whether the Japa-j\nnese military clique has formulated sinister de-1\nsigns or whether there is something like an un\nderground organization in Japan, primed to1\ntake advantage of any opportunity that may\narise.\nNOT TO BE DEFIED\n\"One of the great and irrevocable truths\nseems to have dropped out of our thinking. It\nis the fear of God.\" This unusual remark was\nmade by the Congressman-philosopher, Hat\nton Sumners of Texas, at the House luncheon\ntable recently. \"There are great moral and\nnatural laws of which He is the Author and\nthat are as constant as those to which the vast\nUniverse responds. They are designed to pro\nmote human well-being and progress, and do,\nso long as we obey them. But if a person\njumps from a ten-story window the law of\ngravity is not suspended to save him. Neith\ner are these laws when we go counter to them.\nThey are not to be defied except at the cost of\npain and tragedy, as has been abundantly\ndemonstrated of late.\n\"We need to restore the word 'fear' in its\n|right sense to our thinking\u2014fear of breaking\nithe laws of God. And then, for our own good,\nI to study and discover these laws and adjust\nour affairs to them\u2014in international matters,\nin Government, in our day-to-day relations.\"\nIt is a view substantiated by many passages\nin the Bible, among them this in Proverbs ix,\n10:\nThe fear of the Lord is the beginning\nof wisdom; and the knowledge of the\nholy is understanding.\n\u2014Coutry Gentleman\nI The atomic bomb may be a miracle to some\nj people but to scientists who unravelled the\ni secrets of nature it represents the reward that\nalways accompanies perseverance and intell\nigence, skillfully utilized.\nSoldiers and sailors, coming home from the\nwars, should be heartily welcomed by people\nat home who took none of the risks of defend\ning the nation.\nVarious book publishers are now racing to\nproduce the first complete history of World\n|War two; our advise, if you it or a history, is\nj to wat a while.\nThe Everyday\nCounselor\nBy Rev. Herbert Spaugh, D. D,\nj How long are we going to con\ntinue to demand the right to drink\ni poison which makes men a menace\njto society? If a man takes strych\nJnine, it kills him, it doesn't make\nI him go out and kill people. But let\na man get enough liquor in him,\niand there is no telling to what\nj length he will go toward endanger\ning the lives of others.\nj What about the UP dispatch from\nSeattle, Washington, which tells of\ndrink-sodden 47-year-old veteran of\nboth world wars who beheaded his\nwife with a Bolo Knife?\nThe ex-soldier told a fantastic\nstory, \"of drunken quarrels in\nwhich the couple would cut one an\nother, but never too bad.\" He was\npronounced \"perfectly sane\" by a\npolice psychiatrist.\nA witness to the killing said that\nthe wife ran from her home, pur\nsued by her husband, but was fell\ned by blows from the knife. Scream\ning for help, she struggled to her\nfeet but was beaten to her hands\nand knees and decapitated. The in\nstrument of execution was a three\npound razor-edge Philippine cere\nmonial beheading knife with a \"gro\ntesquely and intricately carved\nstained bone handle,\" more than a\nfoot and a half long from handle to\nblade tip.\nThe accused admitted that he and\nhis wife \"used to get real drunk and\ngrab our big bolo knives and fight\nwith them. We would cut one an\nother, but never too bad. We re\nspected each other's ability to pro\ntect ourselves. We would also shoot\nat each other with guns, but we\nwould never hit one another. We\nnever really aimed because we knew\nwe could hit\" and kill at will. She\nwas a crack-shot.\"\nThis story, published in the Wins\nton-Salem Sentinel, ought to shock\njat lease some of those who have so\nfar failed to see where this nation\njis heading with its growing con\nsumption of alcoholic liquors. Ad\nvertisements scream at us from\nmagazines, newspaper and bill\nboards, extolling beers, wines and\nliquors.\nWe tried to legislate it out of ex\nistence and failed. Now we are\nj trying to regulate it with the same\ni results. Until we get'it into our\n[heads and hearts that alcohol as a\nbeverage is a deadly poison which\nturns men and women into devils,\nland learn to leave the stuff alone,\nj we are going to continue to have\ngruesome stories such as this.\nI We have been horrified at Japa\nnese and German brutality. It\ndoesn't make sense when we con\ntinue to traffic in and make use\nof stuff which transforms human\nbeings into wild beasts, who can be\njust as brutal. j\nOUR DEMOCRACY byMal I\nCommunity Cooperation\nWhen in pioneer davs a family needed a home,\nPEOPLE FROM THE WHOLE COUNTRYSIDE CAME\nTO HELP IN THE HOUSE-RAISING* WITH MANY HANDS\nAT WORK, OFTEN A FAMILY- HOMELESS IN THE\nMORNING \u2014HAD THE PROTECTION OF ITS OWN\nROOF AT NIGHT- THROUGH COMMUNITY EFFORT\nTHE JOB. WAS DONE.\nIn thousands of American communities this\nSAME SPIRIT OF WORKING TOGETHER INTENSIFIED\nBY WAR- IS FUNCTIONING TODAY. IN U.S.O., RED CROSS,\nIN SALVAGE DRIVES, IN CONSERVATION PROGRAMS\nAND IN THE NATIONAL EFFORT TO PREVENT\nINFLATIONARY PRICE RISES BY SPENDING PRUDENTLY\nAND PUTTING MONEY INTO WAR BONDS,LIFE INSURANCE\nAND SAVINGS ACCOUNTS-COMMUNITY EFFORT Ml PROVING\nA WELL-SPRING OF STRENGTH\nFOR OUR DEMOCRACY.\nFID ST NATIONAL\nPANICS\nMARION. N.C.\nW. R. CHAMBERS, President\nW. L. MORRIS, Vice-President\nJ. N. MORRIS, Cashier\nW. F. GRANT, Assistant Cashier\nLAND EXCHANGE NOTICE\nWestern North Carolina Land\nCompany has applied for exchange\nunder act of March 3, 1925, (43\nStat. 1215) offering 5292 acres in j\nMcDowell County, North Carolina,\ndescribed as: Lying on the waters\nof Paddy's Creek and North Fork of j\nCatawba River, adjoined by lands;\nof the United States and Champion j\ni Paper and Fibre Company, being j\nmore particularly described in deed\ndated August 18, 1888, recorded in\nDeed Book 24, pages 330 to 335 in\nclusive, Register of Deeds Office for\nMcDowell County, in exchange for\nnot to exceed an equal value of na\ntional forest timber on approxi\nmately 600 acres in Buncombe\nCounty, North Carolina, on the wat\nershed of Andy Branch, being a por\ntion of Forest Service Tract No. 83;\nand approximately 700 acres in\nYancey County, North Carolina on\nHealth and\nHeatrty\nj\nDr. Sophia Brunton\n\nYou Can't Build a Better World\nAnd Ignore God\nThe nations and individuals that\nneglect and defy God shall perish.\nGod's word says so and history has\n'proved its truth. Look at Babylon,,\nthe proudest and most magnificent\ni empire on the face of the earth.\nGod said through Isaiah, \"I will'\nsweep it with the besom of destruc\ntion.\"\nGod also said, \"And Babylon, the\nglory of kingdoms, the beauty of\nthe Chaldees' excellency, shall be\nas when God overthrew Sodom and\nGomorrah. It shall never be inhab\nited neither shall it be dwelt in from\ngeneration to generation. Neither\nshall the Arabian pitch his tent\nthere.\" This has been literally ful\nfilled.\nBefore your every eyes have you\nseen the swift retribution that has\nfallen on Germany and Japan. They\nexalted themselves, and warred\nagainst \u00bbGod and his Holy Book.\nThey descended below the lowest\nand bloodiest of wild beasts. They\nbecame arrogant and as cruel as\ndeamons from the lowest reaches of\nhell.\nHitler and all of his cruel merci\nless brood! Where are they today?\nSome of them who exalted them\nselves above Deity are suicides in\ndishonored graves.\nLook at Himmler, the most fear\ned perhaps of all the scorpion brood\nwhose shadows fell across Germany.\nHe had the power of life and death\nover the cringing people, and sent\nthousands to the torture chambers,\nor had them beaten or starved to\ndeath. He was worth, millions in\nmoney and treasure. It could not\nsave this God\u2014flouting wretch. He\ntook poison.\nFor three days his body lay on\nthe floor of a Nuremberg villa.\nThree soldiers dumped it into a one\nton truck alongside three spades.\nHe was clad only in a British army\nshirt and army blanket which he had\ndraped around himself, when his\nclothes were taken away. He was\nthrown into a hole in the woods.\nOne soldier said, \"Worm go to the\nworms,\" as the dirt was shoveled\nupon him. No mound was left to\nideitify the grave.\nSo perished the great Himmle r,\nvho exalted himself, as did Lucifer,\nibove the stars of God. God took\na hand, and he came swiftly to his\nend. He died like the coward that\n4\nhe was, covered with infamy and\nshame.\nWake up, America. God has\nwonderfully blessed you. He sent\nyour youth to destroy the place\nwhere the Germans were feverish\nly working on the atom to manu\nfacture bombs which would destroy\nBritain, America and every other\ncountry that opposed them. He has\npreserved America. This has not\nbeen done in order that we might\nspend our days in money-getting\nand wouldly amusements.\nHave you been scared into pray\ning while in dire danger, only to\nforget your Maker as soon as you\nfancy that the danger is past? The\nanswers to prayer that have so of\nten delivered men from death, even\nwhen adrift on the ocean in frail\nrafts, have been granted by our\nGod who has dealt so graciously\nwith us.\nLet us in deep humility look up\nto Him in gratitude and thankful\nness for all His mercies. Let us go\nforward to conquer now for right\neousness, truth and sanity in a re\ndeemed America.\nWhen Your\nBack Hurts\"\nAnd Your Strength and\nEnergy Is Below Par\nIt may be caused by disorder of kid\nney (unction that permits poisonous:\nwaste to accumulate. For truly many\npeople feel tired, weak and miserable\nwhen the kidneys fail to remove excess\nacids and other waste matter from th\u00bb\nblood.\nYou may suffer nagging backache*,\nrheumatic pains, headaches, dizziness*\ngetting up nights, leg pains, swelllng\nSometimes frequent and scanty' urina\ntion with smarting and burning is an\nother sign that something is wrong witfci\nthe kidneys or bladder.\nThere should be no doubt that promj>\u00a3\ntreatment la wiser than neglect. UW\nDoan't Pills. It la better to rely on\nmedicine that has won countrywide ap\u2014\nCroval than on something less favorably\nnown. Doan'i have been tried and test\ned many years. Are at all drug stores..\nGet Doan t today.\nDoans Pills\nthe watershed of Hemphill Creek\nand Little Lost Cove, being portion\nof Forest Service Tract No. 17L..\nPersons claiming said properties or\nhaving bona fide objections to such\napplication must file their protests\nwith the Regional Forester, Glenn\nBuilding, Atlanta, 3, Georgia, be\nfore September 25th, 1945.\nWant-ads will work wonders.","height":"31688","width":"21120"}}
